---
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
import { ArrowLeft, Globe, Clock } from "lucide-react";
---

<Layout
  title="Custom Domain on Cloudflare"
  description="How to connect your own domain to your Cloudflare Pages site. Takes about 5 minutes."
>
  <article class="max-w-[800px] mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-20">
    <a href="/guides" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 font-mono text-xs text-muted-foreground hover:text-heading transition-colors mb-10">
      <ArrowLeft className="h-3.5 w-3.5" />
      All guides
    </a>

    <header class="mb-12 pb-10 border-b border-border">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
        <div class="h-11 w-11 rounded-md bg-primary/10 border border-primary/20 flex items-center justify-center">
          <Globe className="h-5 w-5 text-primary" />
        </div>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-muted-foreground border border-border rounded-full px-2.5 py-1">
          <Clock className="h-3 w-3" />
          5 min
        </span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="font-mono text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold text-heading leading-[1.05]">
        Custom Domain <br />on Cloudflare
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-foreground leading-relaxed">
        How to connect your own domain (like <code class="font-mono text-heading bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">yourname.com</code>) to your Cloudflare Pages site.
      </p>
    </header>

    <div class="space-y-10 text-foreground leading-relaxed">
      <section>
        <h2 class="font-mono text-2xl font-semibold text-heading mb-4">1. Open your Pages project</h2>
        <p>
          Go to <a href="https://dash.cloudflare.com" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:underline">dash.cloudflare.com</a>,
          pick your Pages project, and open the <strong class="text-heading">Custom domains</strong> tab.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-mono text-2xl font-semibold text-heading mb-4">2. Add your domain</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          Click <strong class="text-heading">Set up a custom domain</strong> and enter the domain you want to use
          (apex like <code class="font-mono text-heading bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">yourname.com</code> or a
          subdomain like <code class="font-mono text-heading bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">www.yourname.com</code>).
        </p>
        <p>
          If your domain's DNS is already managed by Cloudflare, the record will be added automatically.
          Otherwise, Cloudflare will show you the exact DNS record to create at your registrar.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-mono text-2xl font-semibold text-heading mb-4">3. Wait for SSL</h2>
        <p>
          Cloudflare provisions a free SSL certificate automatically. This usually takes under a minute,
          but can occasionally take longer. Once it's active, your site will be live on the custom domain.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-mono text-2xl font-semibold text-heading mb-4">4. Update Hakuto config</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
          Update <code class="font-mono text-heading bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">.hakuto/config.json</code> with your domain so Astro generates correct absolute URLs for sitemaps, canonical tags, and social images:
        </p>
        <pre class="font-mono text-sm bg-background border border-border rounded-md p-5 overflow-x-auto text-heading"><code>{`{
  "domain": "yourname.com",
  "siteName": "Your Site"
}`}</code></pre>
      </section>

      <section class="border-t border-border pt-8">
        <p class="text-muted-foreground">
          That's it. Push to main and your site is live on your domain.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
